name: The Troop
overview:
The Troop is an American-Canadian live-action, single camera comedy-adventure television series about a trio of teenagers who fight and capture monsters and other supernatural phenomena that invade the fictional town of Lakewood. Created and executive produced by Max Burnett, Greg Coolidge and Chris Morgan, the series premiered on Nickelodeon on September 18, 2009.

The second season premiered on June 25, 2011 and Nickelodeon cancelled the series midway through its second season. The remaining episodes of season 2 were aired on Nicktoons with the series finale airing on May 8, 2013.

episodes.name: Welcome to the Jungle
episodes.overview: Jake is initiated into The Troop, a group that protects the town from alien monsters. His first mission is to help his mean neighbors, who have been turned to stone.

episodes.name: Do the Worm
episodes.overview: While saving a Senior Dance from a Mongolian death worm, Jake learns not to judge a book by its cover, and Felix becomes an unlikely hero.

episodes.name: There Is No I in Monster Hunter
episodes.overview: Jake learns the value of teamwork. Meanwhile, Hayley finds out that it's not possible to be liked by everyone.

episodes.name: Forest Grump
episodes.overview: A tree monster takes the form of a student in order to kill the student council. Also, Felix is forced into a situation where he must protect a boy that has wronged him in the past.

episodes.name: Pajama Game ... Of Death
episodes.overview: Jake and Felix must infiltrate Hayley's cheerleader slumber party in order to find out which girl is hosting a bug alien. Also, Stockey is nervous about attending his Troop class reunion.

episodes.name: Taming of the Cube
episodes.overview: While fighting a gelatinous cube monster, Haley and Jake accidently switch bodies.

episodes.name: No More Master Nice Guy
episodes.overview: Haley becomes suspicious when a mousy classmate suddenly gains status and power - which is revealed to be by controlling an invisible, subservient monster.

episodes.name: The Great Punkin
episodes.overview: On Halloween night, The Troop has to capture the monsters after the security system breaks down and the monsters escape.

episodes.name: Tentacle Face
episodes.overview: Jake meets his monster-hunting hero, but discovers he's out growing the ability to hunt and capture the ultimate monster he has been chasing his whole career.

episodes.name: Lost in Translation
episodes.overview: A Troop from Japan arrives to share monster-hunting techniques with our Troop, but cultural differences complicate everyone's attempts at defeating the elusive Noctem.

episodes.name: The Good, The Bad and the Ickie Doll
episodes.overview: Jake and Hayley discover that the hot Christmas toy, the "Ickie Doll", has been invaded by a Vapor Monster, turning the dolls into nasty, violent, living creatures.

episodes.name: The Substitute
episodes.overview: When a veteran Troop member named Bianca Stonehouse replaces Mr. Stockley due to his dentist appointment, The Troop discover that she is a monster in disguise, there to help another monster escape and to find the real Bianca Stonehouse before its too late.

episodes.name: Unpleasantville
episodes.overview: A strange Swarm monster causes everyone in town to behave perfectly, The Troop learns that perfection is overrated.

episodes.name: My Gus is Back & There's Gonna be Trouble
episodes.overview: Felix's new friendship with Gus creates a rift within The Troop. Little does anyone know of Gus's secret plans to destroy The Troop.

episodes.name: Speed
episodes.overview: Jake and Haley must pretend to be a couple in order to catch the Eris Fairy(Victoria Justice) that's been running around the school breaking up couples in love. Felix works furiously to trap the Eris Fairy only to realize how much he relates to her situation. In the end, the fairy apologizes to Felix and tells him that she likes him.

episodes.name: I, Monster
episodes.overview: The Troop is in lockdown until they can figure out which one of them is really a monster.

episodes.name: Like A Moth to the Spotlight
episodes.overview: While hunting a Vampire Moth, the Troop must alleviate the suspicions of two of their classmates who witnessed a monster fight, but cannot be Snarked.

episodes.name: Vampsters
episodes.overview: When a group of part vampire/ part Hamster/ part Human monsters invade Lakewood, Jake must go undercover to infiltrate the group in order to find their lair.

episodes.name: Snarked Up
episodes.overview: Jake is pregnant with a baby Snark, which makes his neck look weird. A griffin is harassing local ranchers and Haley and Felix have to take it out.

episodes.name: Itty Bitty Baby Dragon
episodes.overview: After Phoebe unwittingly "adopts" a baby Dragon and Jake and the Troop must figure out how to return it before the mother dragon finds them first.

episodes.name: The Wrath of the Wraith
episodes.overview: Jake and two other students attempt to stay overnight in an abandoned hospital rumored to be haunted by a Wraith.

episodes.name: Hayley and Felix on the Side
episodes.overview: When Haley and Felix are scratched by a Zylork, its venom makes them want to be eaten by the monster and Jake must save his friends from themselves.

episodes.name: Double Felix
episodes.overview: Felix creates a robotic version of himself that is better at his life than he is, but evil. Hayley is bitten by a monster which gives her symptoms that make her seem very nerdy.

episodes.name: Don't Talk to Dr. Cranius
episodes.overview: A Harvard-educated sponge named Dr. Cranius (voiced by Kelsey Grammer) is captured by The Troop. He then tries to manipulate the members so he can escape.

episodes.name: Batteries Not Included
episodes.overview: Mr. Stockley is the acting Principal at school and wants to the day to go perfectly to show off what he can do, but when an Oculypse escapes from HQ havoc is wreaked on the student body.

episodes.name: The Next Stop: Lakewood
episodes.overview: Gus is back from the mental hospital and he plans on destroying The Troop and taking over Lakewood. But in order to do he kidnaps Mr. Stockley, to enter headquarters and release all the captive monsters.

episodes.name: The Triangle
episodes.overview: The troop has its long awaited return and it is full of surprises!!! Jake decides to ask out Hayley but has a tough time especially since she is dealing with the new girl, who is a bad chick. Meanwhile, Felix tours a special school.

episodes.name: The Monster Within
episodes.overview: Everyone thinks Felix is a crime stopper. Meanwhile, Candace and Hayley start to become friends.

episodes.name: It's All in the Game
episodes.overview: Kirby comes to takes Felix's place and must take down a monster who is taking over the mind of video-gamers.

episodes.name: Mirrors
episodes.overview: Candace is attacked by a monster that sucks people into mirrors. So Hayley and Kirby must stop it before it attacks anyone else. Meanwhile, Jake tries to get his comic approved by Stanley Lee.

episodes.name: Oh Brother
episodes.overview: Kirby's replacement is not what the Troop had in mind. Meanwhile, Candace and Hayley have a fight over telling Candace her secret and Candace's brother comes to visit.

episodes.name: Through the Looking Glass
episodes.overview: In the previous episode Jake broke open the portal to bring Candace to the Monster World. But, this releases Monsters into the real world. Now, Jake must go into the real world to retrieve the troop grid.

episodes.name: Start me up
episodes.overview: Kirby enters the science fair and so does his rival from hos old troop who uses a monster for her project which is a robot that attacks the school. Meanwhile, Jake and Hayley battle for concert tickets.

episodes.name: This Bird You Cannot Change
episodes.overview: A Flying Swamp Monster that feeds on electrical energy has come to Lakewood and is not only terrorizing the city but is also threatening Prom from happening.

episodes.name: A Sniff Too Far
episodes.overview: A Flaying Pincer Mole has been attacking the school repeatedly and the only way to find its lair is to team up with the Sniffer... an incredibly annoying monster.

episodes.name: Eris Returns
episodes.overview: Cecilia, an Eris Fairy sister (Daniella Monet) arrives and mistakens Etienne for Felix and they become a couple. Cecilia's ex-boyfriend, Tod comes from the monster world to get her back and get rid of Etienne. Meanwhile, Jake wants to ask Hayley go to the dance with him.

episodes.name: Road Trip (aka
episodes.overview: Jake ,Hayley and Mr. Stockley get a distress call from another Troop team during driver's ed training. Jake and Hayley kiss. Meanwhile Kirby runs for Green Czar and Cadence helps him win against Mazie (Ashley Argota).

episodes.name: The Prisoner of Lakewood
episodes.overview: A monster switches places with Hayley and realizes it easier to be a monster then a teenage girl. Kirby gets trained hard to become a good member of the Troop.

episodes.name: Ice Hassles
episodes.overview: A Flying Swamp Monster that feeds on electrical energy has come to Lakewood and is not only terrorizing the city but is also threatening Prom from happening.
